solidifiers.translation:
solidifier
n.
solidify的变形
solidify
[sə'lidifai]
vt.
使团结，使一致：
Then their ideas were solidified.
此后，他们的思想统一了。
使充实，使巩固；使稳固：
to solidify one's ideas
充实思想
His rule was solidified with the policy of carrot and big stick.
胡萝卜加大棒的政策使他的统治更加巩固了。
使凝固，使固化：
Any liquid could be solidified under the certain conditions.
任何液体在一定条件下均可固化。
使结晶
vi.
团结，一致：
The public opinion may solidify.
公众舆论也许会一致起来。
